This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a method for controlling the level sets of neural networks, which is a fundamental property of classifiers in machine learning. Additionally, the paper also presents results on improving generalization to unseen data, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

The paper also involves tasks related to computer vision (such as surface reconstruction from point clouds), which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of a sample network to relate the level set samples to the network parameters suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which involves the study of intelligent agents and their decision-making processes. 

The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which involves the study of neural networks and their applications. 

Finally, the paper involves the reconstruction of curves and surfaces, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics), which involves the study of computer graphics and visualization.
